{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a8e08a6f-93bc-477f-86cc-3d97fddad4d6","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform, VSTest arguments are replaced by platform-native switches. You'll also need to add a few NuGet packages to your test project:\n\n**Packages to add:**\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\n**New command:**\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**What changed:**\n\n| VSTest (old) | Microsoft.Testing.Platform (new) |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\nThe `--filter` stays on the `dotnet test` side. Everything after `--` is forwarded to the Microsoft.Testing.Platform test host.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fb11db56-c873-4e06-b60f-b16a15f1c054","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling changes, not a codebase task.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences when moving to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n1. `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n2. `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` (built-in)\n3. `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` (using Microsoft.CodeCoverage)\n\n\n4. `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n5. `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n6. `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, `dotnet test` acts as a wrapper around the test host, so some arguments get passed through differently than they did with VSTest. The newer model handles these diagnostics options natively rather than through the blame collector. the arguments go after `--` when using `dotnet test`. I'm also considering the differences between .NET 8 and .NET 9+, where newer versions have better native integration with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, though on .NET 8 the approach might differ slightly.","outputTokens":1103,"requestId":"3401:2F6FBA:756EAB6:81BD16D:69F3FB45"},"id":"c6e5792d-bf33-4e61-8895-e23dfb925eac","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:01:12.403Z","parentId":"839d03ae-9a05-419e-9718-01b7d3888cb6"}
